</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BCD94236F46FFAB0BFCFA3BFB23F9C5" blockId="56.[189,1398,1531,1593]" pageId="56" pageNumber="57">
The specific name is from the Latin for ‘white’ and ’foot’, referring to the mostly white tarsi of this species. The name is deliberately similar to that of the closely related 
<taxonomicName id="4C72EFA06F46FFAB08AEF9DFFB3BF9C4" box="[1007,1163,1566,1592]" class="Insecta" family="Micropezidae" genus="Mesoconius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="56" pageNumber="57" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="albitarsus">
<emphasis id="B90648316F46FFAB08AEF9DFFB3BF9C4" box="[1007,1163,1566,1592]" italics="true" pageId="56" pageNumber="57">M. albitarsus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
